Ous. In forming the compound possum, note that potis drops is, and that t becomes s before s; as, (potuum) = possum. In the perfect, f oi fui, eto, is dropped after t. The infinitivo posse, subjunctive possem, are shortened forms oi potesse and potes- sem. Possum has no imperative, no future participle, uo pertarid, and no supine ; potens is used only us au adjective. The omitted forms are wanting.
